<DOC><DOCNO> AP900727-0195 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-27-90 1122EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-Siemens     07-27 0135</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Siemens,0142</SECOND><HEAD>Siemens Signs Pact with Robotron Unit</HEAD><DATELINE>FRANKFURT, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Siemens AG said Friday it hassigned an agreement with East Germany's Computer Elektronik DresdenGmbH for the development and production of computer hardware.   CED is a unit of the East German electronics group VEB KombinatRobotron Elektronik of Dresden.   Siemens, a West German electrical and electronics concern, saidthe production of Siemens computers in the Dresden plant will beginon Oct. 1.   The Dresden factory will produce personal and larger computersmainly destined for markets in East Germany, the Soviet Union andother East European countries.   Siemens, which plans to invest more than 1 billion marks or $600million in East Germany in the next two to three years, iscurrently planning more than 30 projects and joint ventures there.</TEXT></DOC>